# Funcmaker

## useful functions
**longtail** will return a function that have a long tail, it can be useful in scoring. it take 3 arguments that showed in the picture below

	longtail(extremum, extreme_point, yield_point)

You can plot the function with the lines below.

	import IndigoPy.Math.Funcmaker as fmk
	import IndigoPy.Math.plot as plot
	b=fmk.longtail(50,30,50)
	plot.functionviewer(b,(0,100))

![function: longtail][longtail]


## combinefunc

**combinefunc** can combine function fragments into a complex function. I have written many functions fragments that can be used here. See the code for more informations. I will update this document later.

	import IndigoPy.Math.Funcmaker as fmk
	import IndigoPy.Math.plot as plot
	b=fmk.combinefunc(((fmk.dec_hill(5,10,4),40,-1),(5,50),(fmk.link_cos(5,10),80,1),(fmk.dec_exponential(10,10),80,1)))
	plot.functionviewer(b,(0,100))

![function: combinefunc][combinefunc]
